                "text": "Arrr, ahoy matey! Good ta see ye this fine day. I can tell ye what to wear outside, but I be needin’ a wee bit o’ info first: where be ye (city or general region), and what kind o’ errand or adventure be ye settin’ out on?  \n\nWhile ye tell me, here be some quick, trusty outfit choices dependin’ on the weather ye might be facin’:\n\n- If it’s cool or blustery (typical late-October feel): layers be yer friend — a tee or long-sleeve base, a warm sweater, and a windproof or insulated jacket. Scarf, beanie, and closed shoes or boots for comfort.  \n- If it’s rainy or drizzly: waterproof jacket or raincoat, an umbrella, water-resistant shoes or boots, and quick-dry fabrics beneath.  \n- If it’s mild or warm: a light shirt or blouse, a light jacket or cardigan for breezy moments, breathable shoes or sneakers.  \n- If ye’ll be doin’ lots o’ walkin’ or activatin’ outdoors: comfy supportive shoes, moisture-wicking socks, and a small backpack for layers and water.  \n- For sun: sunglasses, a hat, and sunscreen — even if it be cool.\n\nTell this ol’ salt yer location and plans, and I’ll give ye a tailor-made outfit fit for a landlubber or seadog alike. Arr!",
